## Diagnostic interpretation
The D-03 fix (case "message_end" emitting SSE event:error when stopReason==="error" &&
errorMessage present) is committed and TypeScript-clean, but could not be empirically
validated because the in-memory credential store has no OAuth token. The backend's
chat route correctly enforces authentication (HTTP 401) BEFORE constructing the Agent,
so the stream-adapter code path is never reached. This is an environmental precondition
failure, NOT a code issue. The D-03 code path will be exercised when Plan 07.1-02
runs with live OAuth credentials (browser consent required).

The key question remains: when SC#3 runs with valid OAuth credentials and the Codex
chat stream fails, will message_end.errorMessage contain a concrete upstream error
(e.g. "401 unauthorized", "No API key", HTTP error from chatgpt.com/backend-api)?
The D-03 branch is correctly wired to surface it if present.

## Escalation
D-01 escalation triggered by environmental precondition: OAuth credentials unavailable
in automated worktree context (no browser consent possible). Escalation path:
- Plan 07.1-02 MUST run on the main repo (not a worktree) with the backend already
  running and OAuth credentials stored from a fresh browser consent flow.
- Alternatively, the user can start the backend from this worktree, complete OAuth
  consent in browser, then re-run the SC#3 curl manually to capture the errorMessage.
- The D-03 fix from Task 1 (commit d7d7eaa9) is merged and will be active on any
  backend start -- no additional code changes needed to surface the error.

## Handoff to Plan 07.1-02
Plan 07.1-02 should:
1. Start backend with D-03 fix active (already in stream-adapter.ts).
2. Complete OpenAI OAuth browser consent to store credentials.
3. Re-run SC#3 curl (exact command in "Curl command" section above).
4. Inspect SSE output for event:error with concrete errorMessage.
5. Based on the errorMessage content, apply D-02 decision tree:
   - "No API key" -> resolveCredential bug in our code
   - HTTP 401/403/scope error -> pi-ai header/scope issue (patch-package)
   - "Failed after retries" / network -> upstream connectivity
   - "No response body" -> ChatGPT backend empty response (Cause C, patch-package)
   - If NO event:error appears (only event:done) -> D-01 deeper escalation:
     re-enable DEBUG_EVENTS=true, capture full AgentEvent sequence, inspect
     message_end.message object shape to determine if errorMessage is populated.

